                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1153 St 2/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-01T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 1—12:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Department’s telegram 94, November 22, 6 p.m. The Spanish Government, acting
                    for oil monopoly, has seized without compensation Alicante installations of
                    Standard Oil subsidiary by order effective today. I have informed Spanish
                    Government that I am aware of seizure and that I am reserving all rights in the
                    premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hammond</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
